        "content": "<p>Do we have the result that a surjective endomorphism of a Noetherian module is injective?</p>",
        "id": 239519579,
        "sender_full_name": "Scott Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1621473173
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For that matter, do we have the \"conventional\" definition of a Noetherian module (increasing chain of submodules stabilizes), beyond the statement that <code>&gt;</code> on submodules is well-founded? I appreciate that these are \"the same\", but presumably it's not considered verboten to use the conventional formulation.</p>",
        "id": 239520151,
        "sender_full_name": "Scott Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1621473649
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There is a theorem along those lines for well founded</p>",
        "id": 239520189,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1621473675
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But not spelled out for <code>is_noetherian</code>.</p>",
